##How to order a safe take-out during a lockdown | Wuhan Daily Book 08

WECHAT china30s

Feature description, a platform that encourages you to write about your life. Founded in March 2011, it has a sandwich writing school and a media platform, China Sandwich, at the same time, we are committed to applying the story to cross-border product design, urban culture excavation, exhibition fair, space creation and other three-dimensional field.

Today is the eighth chapter of the Wuhan Daily Book. There are marketing people in Hankou, freelancers in Wuhan, screenwriters in Huangshi... writing together about their experiences of life during the epidemic, about diet, family reflection, and human observation.

01

When the city is sealed,
How to order a safe take-out

By Unger
Coordinates: Wuhan, Hubei
Occupation: Freelancer

"The last week has entered the peak period of disease, so long as there is rice at home, don't go out! " I locked Ah Huan, who was going to go out to store grain today, and refused to let him go out.

But there are only so many ingredients left, which means we have to "muddle through" eating for a long time.

A box of brine shrimp was found in the freezer of the refrigerator, and the last of the Avocados had reached the point where they could no longer be stored. I rummaged in the Pantry and decided to huddle them together to make "Avocado Shrimp Pasta. ".

When the Pasta was ready, Ah Huan silently pulled all the shrimp into my bowl and began to chew the green and yellow noodles. I knew he did not like to eat shrimp, but did not expect to this "special moment" , he still so have their own insist. I'd rather eat humble pie than eat humble pie.

Sure enough, a few hours later, he cried hungry again, the wind swept away a hand-caught cake, but also a neck to drink a cup of hand-made black coffee.

In the evenings, I routinely scrubbed all delivery platforms to see if there were any stores open that would let us buy some food, and I was still disappointed.

By the way to see if there can be delivered to the store, I Miss Ah Huan did not eat a good lunch, want to buy something for him to play Tooth Festival.

In Times of crisis, picking out a takeout shop is also an art. I first ruled out the nameless small shop, such a shop is likely to rent a small storefront or shop in the building, staff hygiene is difficult to ensure, the channel of food is more difficult to say. Preferably a large brand chain, preferably one I've had in-store or previously ordered. But by this time, the slightly larger brands were on vacation, and none of the stores I used to eat were open.

The only other way to look at it is that in terms of sales, most people's choices aren't going to be any worse. The top few sales on the platform are unknown small fry shop, sales high, but also many poor reviews. After going through the store photos, I gave up.

Ah Huan saw that I had been brushing my cell phone. He leaned over and looked at me. As soon as he saw that I was brushing my take-out food, his eyes lit up.

"Let's order takeout tonight! " A Huan picked up a mobile phone to prepare the posture.

"I dare not order what brand of shop, for fear of unsanitary. " I am very hesitant.

"How about this one! " Ah Huan pointed out an old Xinjiang Barbecue restaurant we had, which had been there since we were in high school, and we went there a few times. At least it's been open for years, and you don't have to worry about the ingredients.

Xinjiang has not been diagnosed in a few cases, the minority, will not be healthy some ah? That's the first thing that popped into my head.

While I was still deciding whether to order or not, Ah Huan said, "I'll order. "

"Oh, so soon? Come on, IT FEELS UNSANITARY! "

"I left a message with the rider, no contact delivery, we'll bring the food in at the door. " Ah Huan adopted an attitude of "I've thought about it, don't worry about it" and immediately jumped into the game world, leaving me with a million thoughts running through my mind, you want to eat it, but you don't want it to be sanitary. And regret that if he wanted to order, he should have told him to order more meat for tomorrow.

The rider arrived sooner than I expected. Ah Huan opened the door when he got the call. The food was in the doorway, and the rider was already standing by the elevator a few meters away.

With a distant "your meal is in trouble" , the rider is in the elevator, and Huan grabs the bag and closes the door.

I quickly rushed to the takeout, Ah Huan got there first, opened the sterile paper towels and began to wipe. The outside of the bag, including all the disposable lunch boxes inside, were wiped down. I don't know if I'm being careful, but at least I'm comfortable with this. I was holding the torn but useless alcohol pad, can only conveniently wipe a Huan on the side of the phone.

So for dinner we had a long-lost Barbecue, lamb kebabs, lamb tendons, baked Tofu, roasted leeks, and Naan bread and lamb dumplings. In order not to waste, we heated up yesterday's leftovers and ate them together. I have no objection to such a wonderful combination of barbecue and White Rice, and AH HUAN ATE IT with Gusto.

"If you can't finish it, you can use it for fried rice tomorrow. " I stuffed a piece of meat in my mouth and chewed it until it was fragrant with oil.

"How can I NOT FINISH IT! " Ah Huan said, throwing a piece of meat into my bowl.

02

After the city was shut down,
I've been on the phone with my father longer than the last 30 years

By Wendy
Coordinates: Wuhan, Hankou
Occupation: Marketing

I didn't have a great relationship with my father. He has a lot of anger towards me, and I have a lot of anger towards him. After many arguments, everyone gave up and kept their distance. So even though we both live in Wuhan, he rarely comes to my house, and we may not even call for months. If anything happens, we use our mother as a go-between.

His insistence on returning to Wuhan on Jan. 5, and his casual attitude toward the epidemic, also made me despair that he was just an old man who would make trouble for his children, not understanding the pressure and energy of his children.

After the outbreak on January 22nd, he rebuffed my offer to take him to my home. In my both anxious and impatient cross-examination, he just said he had a cold, afraid to infect me. For a moment, I was silent, he added hastily: It's just a common cold, a runny nose, no fever, no cough.

In Times of crisis, people always want to huddle for warmth or escape, but this virus only the opposite way, full isolation, cut off the source of infection is the best strategy at present. I knew in my heart, but I was really worried that he might be infected.

The first thing I did when I woke up was to call him, and I began to have a common topic, to talk about his cold symptoms, to talk about the common cold symptoms, to talk about the common cold symptoms, to talk about the news on TV. You can talk for an hour without even knowing it.

He would worry that I would have to go out on duty, there is the risk of infection, a variety of believe that the rumors one by one to me, I pay attention to protection.

I worried that he would be bored alone, so I asked my sister to send him more videos of her daughter frolicking and to show him the smiling faces of her nieces.

After the siege, my father and I talked on the phone for more than the previous 30 years.

03

Don't watch the news,
All I care about is what's right in front of me

By Wang Guima
COORDINATES: Wuchang
Occupation: Children's book editor

When you're not watching the news, you suddenly have no desire to express yourself. Without the emotional stimulation of gossip, you'll find that what really matters to you is your daily meals, how you spend your time at home, and whether your friends and family are okay. The "far away" that is out of reach is no longer a source of anxiety, anger and pessimism, but a focus on yourself and those around you. It felt good, except for the fact that I kept a diary of the outbreak for a few days because the days were so unchanging and I didn't have enough material to keep a diary.

At any given time, people expect the best

Today, once again, the record is met with a rare good weather. Wuhan began to clear up the day before yesterday, before it was only a short sunny moment; today it is enough to bask in a whole day of Super Warm Sun. Even the city closed for days, without the pollution of automobile exhaust and Industrial Exhaust, Wuhan's days are much clearer. Wouldn't it be nice to get out of the house? Perhaps this is the voice of all the people trapped in their homes in Wuhan.

Then, the authorities already know everything, early out of the propaganda posters: The Sun is good, but please do not go out. I don't know why I didn't see it when it first came out?

The lure of the sun is deadly to those who haven't been out in a long time

Several days did not see the news, the changes around the more obvious, the original quiet community began to become lively. The day before yesterday afternoon from the street children playing noise, about two or three children, boys and girls, it seems to be playing what games. The noise was loud and the hustle and bustle went on for a long time. Yesterday morning and ran into upstairs GRANDPA in the community yard around the walk, back and forth to walk a lot of circles, and upstairs in the balcony sun neighbors chat up. Wuhan People's peculiar thick voice and dialect resounded through the whole community building. Today, you can see the take-out riders shuttling back and forth from downstairs, and the sound of playing Erhu in the next unit, as well as the sound of voices in some building.

This kind of excitement is especially valuable, as if in another parallel world where there is no epidemic.

Reluctant to let such a good warm sun was wasted, decided to Sun side in the balcony while eating. Just bought has not been able to use the baking dish is still new, might as well eat a barbecue with the sun. Stock up on ingredients, and there's plenty of barbecue food in the house. CIBA soaked in cold water, tricholoma left unfinished two days ago, Green Shanghai Green and in season cabbage leaves; there are two days to eat noodles hotpot left square ham, years ago bubble tender shoot dry. The highlight, of course, is beef and plum strips, with a small amount of tendons cut into thin slices along the horizontal lines, pickled with pepper and fine salt for a while, you can put on a plate to eat.

Rare. No wine today. It took three hours to cook and bask in the Sun.

The whole process, no cell phone messages, no network interference, focus on a vegetable in front of a dish, a hot soup, or even a piece of meat.
And when you're done, you're satisfied.

04

Loving distance

By Xiaoman
Coordinates: Xu Dong, Wuhan
Occupation: New Media

The other day, I was chatting with my sister on Wechat, who was returning to Yichang before the city closed. After checking in, she said they were going back to Wuhan in a few days to bring us some root buds (also known as Herba Houttuyniae, or folded-ear root) , he added, "leave it by the door, and you can take it. ".

This reminds me of this morning when I overheard a conversation between my next-door neighbor and her mother. Looks like her mom brought them Greens.

"Don't run away, we have food, everything, " the neighbor said impatiently through the door.

"This is fresh vegetable Moss, you quickly fried to eat, and you put on the door! "

"I said don't run, don't run, we have food, Wash your hands when you go back, don't touch anything, just leave it at the door, I'll come and get it. "

Because of the outbreak, people are being quarantined. At home, I try to keep my parents at a distance of more than 2 meters, because I still have a little cough, and feel close to them can not help but nervous, but will cough more.

Although the familiar family members miss each other, worry, but are trying to maintain such a "safe distance" , this distance is not indifference, just love and care for each other.

05

The Mask became a fixture on the chin

By Cast
COORDINATES: Huangshi, Hubei
Occupation: Screenwriter Douyin

It's a new day. The Sun is up. Finally because took express out of the door, happened to check the community staff epidemic prevention. Several non-staple food stores and small restaurants opened their doors. The staff advised the owners of the small restaurants and small shops to close first. These days are the peak period of the virus outbreak. Many big parents without awareness of prevention come to buy things without wearing masks and order dishes, as a possible source of infection.

Some lonely old people are also poor, not much culture, children and work in the field, after the city is simply unable to return home. They became the most susceptible and disobedient group of people.

I was on the footbridge to Huangshi Avenue to take a picture of Huangshi Street in Fengcheng epidemic area. Originally busy streets, now there are few cars running, walking on the road people are even more rare, it is particularly cold and cheerless.

Life is far more exciting than the movies, which highlight the deadly places where the virus has broken out, while in reality some elderly people still go about their daily routine, continuing to gather in the park outside their homes to bask in the sun and chat in peace and quiet, it's just a face mask hanging from my chin.

06

In the evening my mother cut my grandmother's hair,
She looks like a lovely child

By Haylin
COORDINATES: Jiyu Bridge, Wuhan
Occupation: freelance dramatist

My grandmother was a native gardener. She had a local accent that no one understood except her mother. And she's been a Christian since she was Middle Age, and she's very different from US ideologically. Every time her children back home she would pull everyone to pray, before she is in good health, pull the whole family to pray for two hours a kneeling, want us to convert to God, make everyone very resist and avoid.

Now that grandma is 91, she probably doesn't have the will to convert the whole family, but she does often persuade us to pray and read the Bible. My attitude toward my grandmother began to change as she got older: from wanting to run away, afraid that she would drag me through the Bible for three hours, to now caring and cooperative, sometimes singing hymns with her. But if it hadn't been for this epidemic, if it hadn't been for the fact that my busy life had to stop, I wouldn't have made the decision to spend time with my grandmother, Doddo, ahead of my other goals.

At noon when my grandmother finished eating, I put her up and walked around the house, she sat every day, such a walk has been Gasp, but I have a sense of accomplishment, because the elderly to maintain a proper exercise is the best maintenance. She was grinning from ear to ear when she saw how close I was to her. I think grandma is actually very easy to feel happy, her life is very simple, so her wish is very simple, that is, want us to spend more time with her.

Grandma sings hymns, no matter what kind of song, it's the same key. Today, she asked me to sing two more hymns. Knowing a little about music, I turned on the piano and played the music. As a result, the songs changed from boring to beautiful. I Sang a few hymns obediently, my Grandmother's mood had changed from being stuck in the city to feeling better. She had always believed that God would not give up on the pious and sing to make her feel that God would keep us safe, even though there was no scientific basis for it, but it was worth it to reassure grandma. My mother cut my grandmother's hair in the evening. She looked like a lovely child.

Finally, my grandmother and we watched a movie, the movie she does not understand, so I have to explain to her from time to time. She doesn't know how to use a cell phone, and she doesn't understand a lot of mandarin, so there's really no entertainment in life for her. Going for a walk was one of her few activities, and now it's banned.

Grandma at home, we are in the epidemic period can not help but watch the phone every day to brush the news of the neighborhood news, I often see grandma sitting there and no one to talk to, it will be very self-reproach. She is so old, in addition to sitting, daze is lying to sleep, then is coughing, choking on water, and the outside world with the same frequent contact and communication, so it is very lonely.

I didn't ask grandma if you were lonely, but I'm sure she'd love for us to put down our phones and spend some time with her.

Grandma at home, we are in the epidemic period can not help but watch the phone every day to brush the news of the neighborhood news, I often see grandma sitting there and no one to talk to, it will be very self-reproach. I didn't have a great relationship with my father. He has a lot of anger towards me, and I have a lot of anger towards him. After many arguments, everyone gave up and kept their distance. So even though we both live in Wuhan, he rarely comes to my house, and we may not even call for months. If anything happens, we use our mother as a go-between.

After the outbreak on January 22nd, he rebuffed my offer to take him to my home. In my both anxious and impatient cross-examination, he just said he had a cold, afraid to infect me. For a moment, I was silent, he added hastily: It's just a common cold, a runny nose, no fever, no cough.

My grandmother was a native gardener. She had a local accent that no one understood except her mother. And she's been a Christian since she was Middle Age, and she's very different from US ideologically. Every time her children back home she would pull everyone to pray, before she is in good health, pull the whole family to pray for two hours a kneeling, want us to convert to God, make everyone very resist and avoid.

Now that grandma is 91, she probably doesn't have the will to convert the whole family, but she does often persuade us to pray and read the Bible. My attitude toward my grandmother began to change as she got older: from wanting to run away, afraid that she would drag me through the Bible for three hours, to now caring and cooperative, sometimes singing hymns with her. But if it hadn't been for this epidemic, if it hadn't been for the fact that my busy life had to stop, I wouldn't have made the decision to spend time with my grandmother, Doddo, ahead of my other goals.

I think grandma is actually very easy to feel happy, her life is very simple, so her wish is very simple, that is, want us to spend more time with her.

Grandma at home, we are in the epidemic period can not help but watch the phone every day to brush the news of the neighborhood news, I often see grandma sitting there and no one to talk to, it will be very self-reproach. She is so old, in addition to sitting, daze is lying to sleep, then is coughing, choking on water, and the outside world with the same frequent contact and communication, so it is very lonely.

I didn't ask grandma if you were lonely, but I'm sure she'd love for us to put down our phones and spend some time with her.
